<p>At 19”x10”x13”, this cat carrier is generously sized to accommodate bigger cats weighing up to 22 pounds. It also comes in a Small/Medium size that measures 17”x8”x11.5”.</p>
<p>Unlike many cat carriers that have a rectangular shape, this carrier tapers from a width of 10 inches at the bottom to 7 inches at the top. This design makes it a less cumbersome to carry and the added height gives your cat a little extra headroom if they want to sit up.</p>
<p>The carrier is constructed from sturdy polyester with large mesh panels for ventilation. The bottom of the carrier is lined with removable, machine-washable sherpa pad. Customer reviews indicate that the materials may not be heavy-duty enough for anxious cats who try to escape, but the carrier works very well for trips to the vet.</p>
<p>Because the carrier has flexible sides, it can be slightly compressed to fit under the seat for air travel. The Small/Medium size might work best for air travel, however, because the height of the Medium/Large carrier might make it too big for some airline under-seat requirements.</p>
<p>Not that this isn’t a crash-tested carrier and it doesn’t have any dedicated restraint straps, so it might not be the safest choice for car travel.</p>
<p>In terms of general function, one customer commented that the carrier was tall and long enough that his 14-pound Maine Coon was able to comfortably sit up or lie down. Another customer with a 20-pound cat found that his cat liked the carrier so much the cat began taking naps in it.</p>
